  <div class="text-block">
    <h2>Visual Design</h2>
    <p>The typography has a techy feel that relates the types of programs BreakLine offers. In terms of color palette, the use of blues and teals provide a calmness and sense of reassurance to balance out the feelings of anxiety and stress that someone who is looking into shifting careers might be feeling. The gradients signify the idea of BreakLine providing their students with a smooth transition into a new career. The application is designed as a step form not only to break it up into shorter, less daunting sections, but also allowing applicants to easily save their changes and come back later.</p>
